"""
train_gpt_submit.py — Submission: larger vocab + longer context + higher throughput.

Changes from previous submission
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Batch tokens  : 524,288  →  786,432  (768 K, satisfies 760 K+ target)
  Sequence len  : 1,024    →  2,048
  Vocab size    : 1,024    (unchanged)
  MLP mult      : 3.0      →  2.5      (offsets the 3× larger embedding so the
                                        compressed model stays ≤ 15 MB)
  RoPE base     : 10,000   →  50,000   (better positional coverage at 2 K ctx)
  Eval stride   : 64       →  128      (proportionally scaled for 2 K context)

Size analysis (all-ranks; world_size × grad_accum always = 8)
  local_tokens per micro-step = 786,432 / 8 = 98,304
  sequences per micro-step    = 98,304 / 2,048 = 48   (exact, no remainder)
  val local_batch_tokens      = 524,288 / 8 = 65,536 ≥ 2,048 ✓

Model params (proposed)  ≈ 21.0 M  →  est. ~14.3 MB quantised + compressed
  Embedding  (int8)       :  4,096 × 512 = 2,097,152 params (+1.57 M vs old)
  MLP hidden (×9 layers)  :  2.5 × 512  = 1,280  (–256 vs old 1,536)
  Attn matrices unchanged :  Q/K/V/O per layer
"""

